est Actress \u2013 Television Series Musical or Comedy\n|{{won}}\n|<ref name=\"Bershire, Mike Schur Talks President\" />\n|-\n|Writers Guild of America\n|Television: Comedy Series\n|{{nom}}\n|<ref name=\"Writers Guild Award Winners\" />\n|-\n|[[American Comedy Awards]]\n|Best Comedy Actress\n|{{won}}\n|<ref name=\"Gale, Newsmakers\" />\n|-\n|[[MTV Movie Awards]]\n|[[MTV Movie Award for Best Cameo|Best Cameo]]\n|''Anchorman 2: The Legend Continues''\n|{{nom}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vulture.com/2014/03/this-is-the-end-and-anchorman-2-earn-mtv-movie-award-nominations.html|title='This Is the End' and 'Anchorman 2' Earn MTV Movie Award Nominations|last=Wright|first=Megh|date=2014-03-06|website=Vulture|language=en-us|access-date=2020-01-11}}</ref>\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|Critics' Choice Television Awards\n|[[Critics' Choice Television Award for Best Comedy Series|Best Comedy Series]]\n|''Broad City''\n|{{nom}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ew.com/article/2014/05/28/critics-choice-television-awards-nominees/|title=Critics' Choice TV Awards 2014: And the nominees are...|last=Bacle|first=Ariana|date=May 28, 2014|website=Entertainment Weekly|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191002202846/https://ew.com/article/2014/05/28/critics-choice-television-awards-nominees/|archive-date=October 2, 2019|access-date=2019-10-28}}</ref>\n|-\n|Best Actress in a Comedy Series\n|rowspan=\"4\"|''Parks and Recreation''\n|{{nom}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.criticschoice.com/television-awards/2014-winners-from-the-4th-annual-critics-choice-television-awards/|title=2014 // Winners and Nominees from the 4th Annual Critics' Choice Television Awards|last=|first=|date=June 1, 2015|website=Critics' Choice Awards|language=en-US|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180115171620/http://www.criticschoice.com/television-awards/2014-winners-from-the-4th-annual-critics-choice-television-awards/|archive-date=January 15, 2018|access-date=2020-01-11}}</ref