ehler-nominated-grammy-award-846350|title=Grammys: Amy Poehler Nominated for 'Yes Please' Audio Book|last=Lewis|first=Hilary|date=December 7, 2015|website=The Hollywood Reporter|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190427182117/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/amy-poehler-nominated-grammy-award-846350|archive-date=April 27, 2019|url-status=live|access-date=April 27, 2019|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n|-\n|Primetime Emmy Awards\n|[[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Guest Actress in a Comedy Series|Outstanding Guest Actress in a Comedy Series]]\n|''Saturday Night Live''\n|{{won}}\n|<ref name=\"Emmy bio, Amy Poehler\" />\n|-\n|rowspan=4|2019\n|Women in Film\n|Entrepreneur in Entertainment\n|\n|{{won}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2019/film/awards/women-in-film-recognizes-shift-in-show-business-1203238675/|title=Women in Film Gala Recognizes Seismic Shift in Showbiz|last=Clement|first=Nick|last2=|first2=|date=2019-06-12|website=Variety|language=en|access-date=2019-06-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190613155228/https://variety.com/2019/film/awards/women-in-film-recognizes-shift-in-show-business-1203238675/|archive-date=June 13, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|rowspan=3|Primetime Emmy Awards\n|Outstanding Comedy Series\n| rowspan=\"2\" Russian Doll (TV Series) |''Russian Doll''\n|{{nom}}\n|<ref name=\"Emmy bio, Amy Poehler\" />\n|-\n|Outstanding Writing for a Comedy Series\n|{{nom}}\n|<ref name=\"Emmy bio, Amy Poehler\" />\n|-\n|[[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Host for a Reality or Competition Program|Outstanding Host for a Reality or Competition Program]]\n|Making It (TV series)|''Making It''\n|{{nom}}\n|<ref name=\"Emmy bio, Amy Poehler\" />\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2020\n| rowspan=\"2\" |Writers Guild of America\n|Comedy Series\n| rowspan=\"2\" |''Russian Doll''\n|{{pending}}\n|<ref name=\"2020 Writers Guild Awards Nominees\">{{Cite web|url=https://awards.wga.org/awards/nominees-winners|title=2020 Writers Guild Awards N